          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">SBU sends a message</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-18-1.png" alt="SBU sends a message" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Gen. Igor Kirillov, a top Russian general in charge of the country's radiological, biological, and chemical protection forces, was <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/17/europe/russia-bomb-kills-nuclear-protection-chief-intl-hnk/index.html" target="_blank">killed</a> in Moscow by a remotely detonated bomb planted in an electric scooter outside his apartment building. Ukraine's SBU security service immediately claimed the attack, which comes a day after Kirillov was sentenced in absentia by Ukrainian prosecutors for Russia's use of banned chemical weapons in its invasion of Ukraine.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">His death is the highest-profile killing of a Russian military official since the invasion began in February 2022. Ukraine's actions represent a strategic message to Russia's elites. It also brought the <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cm2ek388yxzo" target="_blank">war situation</a> closer to home for the Russians. Many Russians reported a sense of shock from this, as most of what they read about the war in Ukraine from their electronic devices, and it feels so far away. The Russian government has called this an act of terrorism, and the officials seek to punish Ukraine.​</p>
        </mj-text>
